'''Ernest Bernard Jackson, Jr''' (born October 9, 1986) is an [[American football]] [[wide receiver]] who is currently a member of the [[BC Lions]] of the [[Canadian Football League]]. He played [[college football]] at the [[Buffalo Bulls football|University at Buffalo, The State University of New York]] and attended [[Gates Chili Central School District#Schools|Gates Chili High School]] in [[Rochester, New York]]. He has also been a member of the [[Erie Explosion]] of the [[Ultimate Indoor Football League]] and [[Chicago Slaughter]] of the [[Indoor Football League]].<ref name="A">{{cite web | url=http://sports.nationalpost.com/2012/08/21/b-c-lions-ernest-jackson-takes-the-road-less-travelled/ | title=B.C. Lions<U+2019> Ernest Jackson takes the road less travelled | publisher=nationalpost.com | date=August 21, 2012 | accessdate=17 April 2014 | author=Tucker, Cam}}</ref>

